The paper deals with the verification complexity of proof-labeling schemes, which is a topic related to distributed computing and network protocols. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory and information theory concepts, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as possible sub-categories.
